            ************* Interrupt Handling **************


Interrupt:
	* Fastint --> take fastint
	* Resched --> take resched
	* IPI --> check sanity

Are those are the only two options from interrupt handler?

Fastint --> take fastint (in "init" context) --> VMSWI for virtual-machine
  destined interrupts?
	+ removes L2 interrupt controller, non-fastint handlers from kernel
	+ Deciding Phys Int -- Virt Int mapping outside kernel
	- Potentially slower 
	- Potentially don't want VMSWI trap in fastint context

VMSWI --> VM event
  Just a first stab:
  * Set global event pending 
  * Look up VM Event --> VM Handler Thread
  * Set VM Handler Thread->status = NEEDS_VMWORK
  * If VM Handler Thread->mode == RUNNING: IPI;
  * If VM Handler Thread->Mode == READY: nothing
  * If VM Handler Thread->mode == INTWAIT: ready / check sanity
  * If VM Handler thread->mode == Futex: ???

  When thread does vmwork code, if it can take the interrupt it will clear
  the appropriate global interrupt pending bit and take the interrupt.

